Home / Terms and Policies / MiFID


MiFID

The Markets in Financial Instruments Directive ("MiFID" - 2004/39/EC) is a European 
                Directive, which applies to the European Economic Area ("EEA") including all Member 
                States of the European Union as well as Norway, Iceland and Liechtenstein. MiFID's 
                primary objectives are to ensure a single market for financial services, protect investors, 
                foster further competition in the financial services industry and increase market transparency. 
                MiFID concerns almost all financial instruments and investment services, comprising the new 
                architecture for the securities industry across the EEA.
The information displayed on this website concerns investment services provided by BTG Pactual 
                Europe LLP. Here, you will find information on BTG Pactual UK's General Terms and Conditions 
                for Investment Services and its Order Execution Policy.
Investment Services - General Terms and Conditions
Find below BTG Pactual's General Terms and Conditions for Investment Services.


					Pactual Europe LLP - Investment Services General T&C

					MiFID Client Categorisation

					Important Notices

Markets in Financial Instruments Directive - Order Execution Policy
MiFID requires BTG Pactual to put in place an Order Execution Policy and to take all 
                reasonable steps to obtain the best possible result, either when executing orders or when 
                receiving and transmitting orders for execution on behalf of its clients. 

MiFID Order Execution Policy

A non-exhaustive list of the Execution Venues used by BTG Pactual can be found here.

See our Code of Business 
					Principles & Ethics.

The information in this website is subject to change without notice. Nothing in
                it should be interpreted as a solicitation to engage in any investment activity
                in any jurisdiction.




